From Missoula to Flathead Lake to Whitefish to Glacier National Park, and all the unforgettable stops along the way, we come to the end of our Western Montana's Glacier Country road trip. Continue the adventure with our #ExpediaViewfinders by following #PictureMontana and #MontanaMoment.

(Photo credit: Midlife Road Trip)
link_name: Plan an unforgettable road trip in Montana

status_message: From Glacier National Park, we head back to Whitefish on our #PictureMontana road trip and into the heart of Whitefish Trail. Hike any of the diverse trails, each has a unique experience and various lakes with spectacular views. Find out how you can start your Western Montana's Glacier Country adventure here: http://expd.us/picMT

We arrived at Glacier National Park! Take the Going-to-the-Sun Road on a red bus tour and see the massive Lake McDonald, a place once occupied by glaciers that carved out this valley thousands of years ago. Now it's home to stunning sights, hiking trails, boat tours, kayaking and so much more. #ExpediaLovesParks See more of our #PictureMontana road trip here: http://expd.us/picMT

Good morning from Whitefish! Check out this gorgeous view from the The Lodge at Whitefish Lake. Here you can have some water sport fun on the lake or just soak in the fresh air and beautiful colors that make this a perfect #PictureMontana moment. http://expd.us/picMT
How to find something for everyone on Disney Cruise Line. #ExpediaAtDisney

status_message: Feeling swept away by the horses in Flathead Valley. Take a moment to get unplugged and reconnected with nature, and experience all the wonder of the wild. Add in the lush greenery surrounding Flathead Lake, one of the largest freshwater lakes, there's no better way to #PictureMontana.

We came, we saw, we conquered Missoula! From Missoula Int'l Airport to local favorites of downtown, we experienced amazing food, people and places on our urban adventure. Now we're taking off for Ninepipes Lodge and Flathead Lake Lodge! #PictureMontana Follow along on our road trip: http://expd.us/picMT

(Photo credit: Bully)

Who says you can't surf in Montana? Catch surfers and kayakers on Brennan's Wave next to Caras Park on the Clark Fork River in the heart of downtown Missoula. They're even planning to complete a second wave nearby! #PictureMontana Learn more: http://expd.us/picMT

(Photo credit: Girl Gone Travel)

Greetings from the #ExpediaViewfinders on the M at the top of Mount Sentinel! Hike up and enjoy gorgeous views when you Visit Missoula! This is how we #PictureMontana. How about you? http://expd.us/picMT #VisitMissoula #GlacierMT #MontanaMoment

We're off! For a week we'll be on a road trip through Western Montana's Glacier Country exploring the urban, unplugged, undiscovered and unforgettable experiences that Montana has to offer. Follow along with #PictureMontana and stay tuned for some incredible moments leading up to #GlacierMT. First stop: Missoula! http://expd.us/picMT

status_message: Good morning from the Epcot International Flower and Garden Festival! Disney character topiaries, fresh garden food and spring time entertainment have bloomed all around the park. #ExpediaAtDisney 🌷🌻

Last day of our video shoot with Disney Cruise Line! We're filming a series about how to plan and maximize a Disney Cruise vacation. Coming to our YouTube channel this summer! Watch the #ExpediaAtDisney playlist on our channel now to get top tips for a Walt Disney World vacation. Check back this summer for the cruise videos! 🚢🎥
Today we're on deck of the Disney Magic ship shooting a video series with Disney Cruise Line. Add us on snapchat at expedia.com for a behind the scenes look! ✨🎥🐭🚢
Captain Mickey Mouse and the Expedia Viewfinder blog team. On deck of the Disney Fantasy ship! #ExpediaAtDisney

Fireworks lighting up the sky over the Disney Dream ship. Don't miss the Pirates in the Caribbean celebration on Disney Cruise Line. There are appearances from everyone's favorite pirate characters, a stage show, a fireworks display and a dance party to end the night. #ExpediaAtDisney

Serenity Bay on Castaway Cay. This adults-only beach is the perfect retreat during a Disney Cruise. There are plenty of beach chairs and umbrellas, so you don't have to rush to get there in the morning. The sand is soft, the water is clear and there's even a bar and BBQ next door. There's no reason to leave! #ExpediaAtDisney 🌴

Good morning from Disney's private island, Castaway Cay! We arrived this morning via Disney Cruise Line. There are three beaches: two for families and one for adults. A tram connects all of the beaches for easy access. There are lots of water activities to enjoy like sting ray encounters and jet skiing. This is paradise! #ExpediaAtDisney ☀️

The Disney Dream ship all lit up at night. Next year, Disney Cruise Line will sail on new itineraries and to new ports, including first-time visits to four destinations in Alaska and Europe. Amsterdam and Portland, England (the gateway to Stonehenge) are among them. Who's in?! #ExpediaAtDisney 🚢
We woke up to this! The lobby of the Disney Dream ship couldn't be more stunning. Which Disney movie does it remind you of? Look closely and you might spot a familiar face... #ExpediaAtDisney ✨
We're kicking off 10 Days of Disney with Disney Cruise Line! Sailing to the Bahamas on the Disney Dream ship. We'll be live posting insider looks all week. Follow along with #ExpediaAtDisney!

status_message:
Paris Attacks Travel Update

On Friday, November 13th there were a number of attacks in Paris resulting in casualties. Our deepest sympathies go out to those in Paris. 

As a result, France has declared a state of emergency and tightened controls at its borders. Please check the latest information via your local government for advice. If you are due to travel this weekend, please check the status of your flight before travelling to the airport.

Due to extremely heavy call volumes as a result of this incident, we ask that you only contact us if you are in Paris now and need immediate help; or are due to travel to Paris within the next 48 hours. Thank you.
Our hearts go out to Paris and all of those affected today. #PrayForParis

status_message:
"That looks like unicorn poop!" When Captain and Clark traveled to Italy, they found this ridiculously fun dessert. Here's how it tasted:
 
"It wasn't unicorn poop, but instead was a magical masterpiece by one of the best gelaterias not only in Girona, but the world… Unlike traditional scooped Italian gelato, the rich ice cream that's served at Rocambolesc resembles more of an American soft-serve. With a rotating cast of flavors, you'll never know what will greet you upon entering. Ranging from traditional (Tahitian vanilla) to unconventional (carrot, anyone?), the flavors set the scene while the real showstoppers are the accoutrements… Before I indulged in my creation, I did what any seasoned travel blogger would have done: I took a picture and posted it on Instagram. And while one commenter referred to it as unicorn excrement, it tasted like pure magic."

Read the rest of this post on the Expedia Viewfinder travel blog: http://expd.us/ouHpGb
